Kudos Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
January 13, 2025
1. INTRODUCTION
Kudos is committed to protecting the data you share with us. This policy (“Privacy Policy”) describes the ways we collect, store, use and protect personal information we receive from our customers, users and website visitors.
As used in this Privacy Policy, “Personal Data” describes and refers to any information about you. This information can often be used or combined with other information to identify you, contact you, or locate you and includes information such as your name, company name, email address, billing address, payment information, or any other personal information that is provided to us by you, whether mandatory or voluntary.
This Privacy Policy applies to Kudos’ Software-as-a-Service offered via the Kudos Employee Engagement Platform (“Kudos Platform”) including the Kudos mobile application (“Kudos Application” or “Application”), and all Kudos websites (collectively, the “Websites”), as well as other online interactions that you may have with Kudos by or through the Kudos Platform, the Kudos Application, and/or the Websites, including live chat, customer support inquiries, webinars, events, etc. If you do not agree with the Privacy Policy, or with the Kudos Terms of Service accessible at
http://www.kudos.com/terms-of-service
, do not access or use the Kudos Application, Kudos Websites, or any other elements of Kudos’ business.
2. COLLECTION AND USE
The following sections cover the specifics of each of the groups from which Personal Data is collected: (1) Website Visitors and (2) Kudos Platform and Kudos Application Users.
2.1 Website Visitors
If you are a Visitor to our website only (“Visitor”), and not a user of the Kudos Platform or Kudos Application, then this section applies to you. By visiting this Website, you consent to the collection and use of your Personal Data as described herein. If you do not agree with the terms set out herein, please do not access, visit, or use this Website. If required by applicable law, we will seek your consent to process Personal Data collected on this Website or volunteered by you. Kindly note that any consent will be entirely voluntary. However, if you do not grant the requested consent to the processing of your Personal Data, the use of certain sections of this Website may not be possible.
2.1.1 Data collected
Kudos may collect, record and analyze information of Visitors to its Website. We may record part of your IP address (to identify a visitor’s country, state, and city) and use cookies. Kudos may add information collected by way of page-view activity. Furthermore, Kudos may collect and process any Personal Data that you volunteer to us in our Website’s forms and chat interfaces, such as when you request a demo or certain thought-leadership or marketing content from the Kudos Website, such as white papers, case studies, articles, and other materials.
Collected Personal Data may include your IP address (as described above), first and last name, email address, your telephone number, your job title, department, data for social networks, your areas of interest, interest in Kudos products, and certain information about the company you are working for (company name, industry, employee count, and address), as well as information as to the type of relationship that exists between Kudos and yourself.
Kudos also gathers data about visits to the Website, including numbers of Visitors and visits, geo-location data, length of time spent on the site, pages clicked on, page elements clicked on, length of page scrolled, or where Visitors have come from.
2.1.2 Purpose of processing Personal Data
Kudos uses the collected Personal Data to communicate with Visitors, to provide information requested by Visitors, to show ads on other websites to Visitors, and to improve its Website by analyzing how Visitors navigate its Website.
Kudos also collects Personal Data submitted through our Website for the following purposes:
Remembering your preferences on the Website and streamlining your experience such as by pre-filling form fields that you have previously filled in (for instance when requesting white papers)
Identifying potential new client organizations who have interacted with us on our Website
If you have subscribed to receive emails from us, contacting you with educational and informational materials related to the employee engagement and recognition space
2.1.3 How long does Kudos hold my information?
Information submitted on the Kudos Website for the purposes of inquiring about Kudos services, requesting a white paper, or subscribing to receive email updates will be held indefinitely unless we receive a request to delete your data. You may request deletion of your Personal Data from Kudos’ marketing databases by contacting
privacy@kudos.com
.
2.1.4 How can I manage my Personal Data held by Kudos?
If you wish to update, remove, or add to the Personal Data collected by our Website, you may submit your request to
privacy@kudos.com
. Alternatively, if you only wish to view and update your own contact information held by the Kudos Marketing team, you can do so by visiting
https://www.kudos.com/my-data
.
2.2 Platform and Application Users
If you are a registered user with the Kudos Platform or Kudos Application (“User”), then this section applies to you. By using the Kudos Platform and/or the Kudos Application, you consent to the collection and use of your Personal Data as described herein. If you do not agree with the terms set out herein, please do not use the Kudos Platform and/or the Kudos Application. Your Employer is responsible for collecting your explicit consent to process Personal Data collected and used on the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application. If you do not grant the requested consent to the processing of your Personal Data, use of the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application may not be possible. If you do not grant consent to store or process your Personal Data on Kudos, please contact your Employer.
2.2.1 Data collected
When opening your account or creating a new user profile on the Kudos Application, you submit certain Personal Data to us which is associated with your account or user. Mandatory data required for your personal account setup collected includes employee first & last name, email address, for GRS rewards functionality- Country and a unique Employee Number (unique value) /external ID is required. Additional, optional data collected for the purposes of making your profile more interesting and social includes job title, company, birthday, Yammer User ID (if applicable), Zendesk URL (if applicable), location and addresses, profile image, accreditations, personal website and favourites (e.g., favourite movie, musician, etc.), education, family member names, phone number, hometown and biography.
2.2.2 Purpose of processing Personal Data
Kudos uses data collected from the creation and use of a Kudos account to improve use of various features of our service, to collect and report use metrics for your employer to determine overall application adoption within your company, to troubleshoot and debugging the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application, to notify you about changes to the Kudos service relevant to your account or user profile, gather feedback on the Application, and to identify users who submit support tickets in order to provide direct and effective customer support.
Kudos periodically posts customer and user testimonials on our Website which may contain Personal Data such as the customer or user’s name. We always obtain customers’ consent prior to posting the testimonial and their name along with their testimonial. If you want to remove your Personal Data that is being displayed on our Website under public pages, please send your request to
privacy@kudos.com
.
The content of the comments or messages sent by a user through Kudos will be provided and disclosed to that user’s Employer to enable them to identify the user for the purposes of rewards and recognition, performance reviews and coaching. Information that is made public at a User’s discretion by posting to the Team Wall is accessible to all Users within your organization.
We further gather information about the location, device, and operating system used by users of the Kudos Application to guide future development of the service.
2.2.3 How long does Kudos hold my information?
Kudos will retain your Personal Data for as long as reasonably necessary to comply with legal obligations or for as long as required for legitimate business purposes.
Personal Data held in the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application will be stored until an authorized Administrator or Super Administrator from your company initiates data anonymization of your User account. Once your Personal Data has been anonymized, your first and last name will be the only pieces of Personal Data that will remain. This information is held to ensure that any post that you may have sent to others within Kudos will still be associated with a name as well as to ensure administrator reporting on rewards redemptions is accurate. If you wish to have your first and last name removed as well, please notify your Administrator or Super Administrator when you request the anonymization that you would like this data anonymized as well.
2.2.4 How can I manage my Personal Data held by Kudos?
You may update your Personal Data collected by making corresponding changes within the Kudos Platform or the Kudos Application. However, you may alternatively send a request to
privacy@kudos.com
with the information that you wish updated, added, or removed. We will require verification of your identity before making any changes to your account.
2.2.5 What happens to my Kudos account if I leave my company?
The Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application have a built-in function for businesses to delete all Personal Data of employees that have left the company or otherwise do not wish to be a part of the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application. To request that your Personal Data be cleared by your employer for this reason, please contact the department in your organization that is responsible for your Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application account.
2.2.6 What happens if my account is closed by Kudos?
If your account is closed by Kudos due to a violation of the Terms of Service, or at the request of your employer, you may contact us to request the deletion and anonymization of your Personal Data stored in the system. Each request of this type will be examined on a case-by-case basis, and we will act in accordance with legal requirements.
2.2.7 What happens to my data after acquiring a trial Kudos account?
Upon completion of a trial, if your account is not upgraded to a paid account, and instead downgrades to an unpaid, inactive account, your account and all relevant Personal Data will be anonymized and no longer available within sixty (60) days of the date that it was downgraded.
3. SHARING PERSONAL DATA
Kudos may share such Personal Data with service vendors or contractors in order to provide a requested service or transaction or in order to analyze the Visitor behaviour on its Website, the Kudos Platform, and/or the Kudos Application.
In the event that Kudos is acquired or transfers some or all of its operations and/or assets to another organization or entity, that entity will be bound to the same data-protection commitments outlined in this policy and all related policies at the time of acquisition.
In the event that Kudos is acquired or transfers some or all of its operations or assets to another company, information collected, including Personal Data, may be one of the assets so assigned. You consent to such a transfer of your Personal Data, provided that the transferee shall be bound by the terms of the Privacy Policy in effect at the time of its collection.
We will reveal an individual’s Personal Data without prior permission only when we have reason to believe that the disclosure of this information is required to establish the identity of, to contact or to initiate legal proceedings against a person or persons who are suspected of infringing rights or property belonging to Kudos or to others who could be harmed by the user’s activities or of persons who could (deliberately or otherwise) transgress upon these rights and property. We are permitted to disclose Personal Data when we have good reason to believe that this is legally required.
4. COOKIES
Cookies are small pieces of information sent by a website or application to a visitor’s computer. By continuing to visit the Website or to use the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application, you agree to the placement of cookies on your device. If you choose not to accept our cookies, we cannot guarantee that your experience will be as fulfilling as it would otherwise be. We may also place cookies from third parties for functional and marketing purposes. The use of cookies is widespread and benefits the user. For further information, see Kudos Cookie Policy
www.kudos.com/cookie-policy
.
5. LINKS TO OTHER SITES
Please be aware that while visiting our Website or using the Kudos Platform and/or Kudos Application, Visitors and Users can follow links to other sites or services that are beyond our sphere of influence. Kudos is not responsible for the content or privacy policy of these other sites or services.
6. WHERE DOES KUDOS STORE MY PERSONAL DATA?
Data, including Personal Data, collected in the Kudos Application is stored on cloud-based servers located in Canada. By using Kudos, you acknowledge that your Personal Data will be transmitted to, stored, and accessed in Canada. The Kudos Website uses third-party & analysis tracking tools and whose servers may be located in any country in which these third parties have their facilities.
7. HOW DOES KUDOS PROTECT MY INFORMATION?
Personal Data submitted to Kudos either through the Kudos Platform, the Kudos Application, or the Website are encrypted using 256-bit SSL-encrypted connections. The Kudos Application is secure in the cloud and running on data storage infrastructure that has achieved SOC 2 Type II attestation and ISO 27001 certification. ISO 27001 is a widely adopted global security standard that sets out requirements and best practices for a systematic approach to managing company and customer information. The data centres that run the Kudos infrastructure are equipped with video surveillance and detection systems, authorized personnel use multi-factor authentication mechanisms to access data centres, server room entrances are secured with sound alarm devices, with strict personnel access controls and detailed entry logs for visitors. Finally, servers that store customer data are physically and logically separated from the Kudos web application servers.
8. WHO PROCESSES AND WHO CONTROLS MY DATA?
Certain data protection regulations require a distinction between a “Data Controller” and “Data Processor.” With regard to the Kudos Platform and Kudos Application, the customer is considered the Data Controller and Kudos is the processor. Please see Kudos Inc.
Data Processing Agreement
for details. For Personal Data collected by or through the Kudos Website, Kudos is the Data Controller, and the Processor, except in circumstances where the Data Processor is another third-party service.
9. CONTROLLING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
We will not sell, distribute or lease your personal information to third parties unless we have your permission or are required by law to do so.
10. EUROPEAN DATA PROTECTION AND OWNERSHIP
Individuals located in the European Union have a legislated right to change, request deletion of, or know the extent of personal information collected by organizations. Unless required to do otherwise by law, we will honour requests to update, correct, change, or delete Personal Data following successful identity verification.
For Users and Visitors from the European Union, all processing and transferring of Personal Data is performed in accordance with privacy rights and regulations following the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and Kudos’ processing will take place in accordance with the GDPR. Kudos has adopted reasonable physical, technical and organizational safeguards which substantially mirror the EU safeguards against accidental, unauthorized or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, disclosure, access, use or processing of the Personal Data in Kudos’ possession. Kudos will promptly notify the User in the event of any known unauthorized access to, or use of Personal Data.
11. DATA PROTECTION OFFICER
Kudos has a “Data Protection Officer” who is responsible for matters relating to privacy and data protection. This Data Protection Officer can be reached at the following address:
‍
privacy@kudos.com
Attn: Privacy Officer
12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may amend this policy at any time by posting a revised version on our website. Please check back occasionally for updates. Please feel free to contact us regarding our privacy policy via email at
privacy@kudos.com
.
